	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001066_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">Barnet 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> July</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I beg to 
<lb/>return you my 
<lb/>hearty thanks 
<lb/>for your work 
<lb/>on Lunars 
<lb/>and the kind 
<lb/>offer which 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001066_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>accompanies 
<lb/>it<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>It is only this 
<lb/>morning that 
<lb/>I have been 
<lb/>able to look at 
<lb/>your note. Some 
<lb/>of my observations 
<lb/>gave discordant 
<lb/>results this 
<lb/>induced me to 
<lb/>send my observation 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001066_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>book to the 
<lb/><persName>Astronomer Royal</persName>
<lb/>to have any 
<lb/>errors of 
<w>trans-<lb break="no"/>cription</w> rectified 
<lb/>and some have 
<lb/>been detected but 
<lb/>as I handed 
<lb/>them over at 
<lb/>once to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Arrowsmith</persName> to 
<lb/>be used in the 
<lb/>map, I don<reg>'</reg>t yet 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001066_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>know their value<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>The sextant was 
<lb/>damaged on board 
<lb/><term type="boat">the Frolic</term> on our 
<lb/>way to <placeName>Mauritius</placeName>
<lb/>&amp; recut so I could 
<lb/>not do what 
<lb/>you suggest.</p>
<lb/><p><choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>hanking you 
<lb/>heartily 
<lb/>for your 
<lb/>kind offer I am</p>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir Yours &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p><addSpan spanTo="#p1r" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='Left margin of fol. 1r'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p>I am to visit <persName>Admiral Smythe</persName> at <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Lee's</persName>
<lb/>could I see you there?</p><anchor xml:id="p1r"/>
			
</div>
